<body>
    <h1>Phishing Awareness Training</h1>
    <h2>What is Phishing?</h2>
    <p>
        Phishing is a type of social engineering attack often used to steal user data, including login credentials and credit card numbers.
    </p>

    <div class="quiz">
        <h3>Quiz: Which of these is a common feature of phishing emails?</h3>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer('A')">A. Asking for personal information</button>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer('B')">B. Sending congratulations messages</button>
        <button onclick="checkAnswer('C')">C. Offering technical support</button>
    </div>
    <p id="result"></p>

    <p onmouseover="showInfo()">Hover over this text to learn more about phishing tactics.</p>
    <div id="info" class="info">
        <p>Phishing tactics often involve creating a sense of urgency to make victims act quickly. Be cautious of emails that claim you must take immediate action.</p>
    </div>

    <script>
        function checkAnswer(answer) {
            let resultText;
            if (answer === 'A') {
                resultText = "Correct! Phishing emails often ask for personal information.";
            } else {
                resultText = "Incorrect. The correct answer is A. Phishing emails often ask for personal information.";
            }
            document.getElementById('result').innerText = resultText;
        }

        function showInfo() {
            document.getElementById('info').style.display = 'block';
        }
    </script>
